main event: A witness observed a bright light in the sky, estimated to be of similar magnitude to Venus or Jupiter, on 6 April 1966.
interesting points: The object was reported to have a steady white color without additional colors or marks.,It moved from zenith to a course heading of 240-350 degrees in a span of 3-5 seconds.,The estimated speed of the object was calculated to be Mach 2 or 3.,The object was seen at an estimated height of 14,000 to 16,000 feet M.S.L.,The conclusion drawn was that the object was an astro (meteor) and no physical evidence was found.
witness description: 21-year-old student currently studying toward a degree in meteorology and/or physics.
